hardest part was defining the unit - I arbitrarily picked 1000 standard queries at 70% MMLU threshold which is the equivalent of a relatively intelligent white collar worker answering 1000 emails, summarizing 1000 news stories, or answering 1000 SAT questions. at ordinary US professional services salaries, the human equivalent is around $1.5k to $5k in labor equivalent. suffice to say the AI model started out cheaper by a factor of 100 which grew to a factor of 200,000x over the following 3 years.

